  "text": "This study investigated the association between CRP concentrations and functional motor deterioration in patients with PD using the Unified Parkinson's Disease Rating Scale Part III (UPDRS-III) score [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The hypothesis, that high plasma CRP concentration would enhance the neurodegenerative process and accelerate functional deterioration in patients with PD, was tested.",
